    • Method Detail

      • CityName

        StringProperty CityName()
        Returns:
        the name of the City this address is located in.

      • City

        LinkProperty<City> City()
        Returns:
        the City this address is located in. Optional but if set then CityName() should be AbstractName.Name().

      • Country

        LinkProperty<Country> Country()
        Returns:
        the Country this Address is located in.

      • Region

        LinkProperty<Region> Region()
        Returns:
        the Region this Address is located in.

      • Zip

        StringProperty Zip()
        Returns:
        the PostalCode as String. Validation depends on the Country.PostalCodeMode().

      • PostalCode

        LinkProperty<PostalCode> PostalCode()
        Returns:
        the PostalCode. Optional but if set then Zip() has to be AbstractCode.Code().

      • PoBox

        StringProperty PoBox()
        Returns:
        the Post Office (PO) box. It is a unique identifier for a locked box typically located on the premises of the post office. In most countries a PO box has a numberic code. However String is used as this is not ensured for all countries. is Has to be present if Street() is empty.

      • Street

        StringProperty Street()
        Returns:
        the street name. Has to be present if PoBox() is empty.

      • StreetNumber

        StringProperty StreetNumber()
        Returns:
        the optional street number or house number. Please note that this is not strictly numeric (e.g. "7b" is a valid value) and is therefore represented as String.
